HEADWORD: Xanthorhamnin
<hw>Xan`tho*rham"nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xantho-</ets> + NL. <ets>Rhamnus</ets>, the generic name of
the plant bearing Persian berries.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
glucoside extracted from Persian berries as a yellow crystalline powder,
used as a dyestuff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

